  "body": "Intro:\r\nIn order to use [RefundableCrowdsale](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/zeppelin-solidity/blob/5cf503673faea92c1b5c615c3f8358febf06e160/contracts/crowdsale/RefundableCrowdsale.sol), you have to have [RefundVault](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/zeppelin-solidity/blob/5cf503673faea92c1b5c615c3f8358febf06e160/contracts/crowdsale/RefundVault.sol)\r\n\r\nI have spotted a few problems:\r\n\r\n1. In order to deposit into the vault, you have to give ownership of vault contract to crowdsale\r\nOnce you do that, you won't be able to call other functions such as `close`, and `enableRefunds` because the owner is crowdsale.\r\nSo, I assume that RefundableCrowdsale is missing a few methods for those proxy calls in order to gain full control of the vault. \r\n\r\nAlso, unit test coverage is very poor for RefundableCrowdsale, not covering all cases. \r\n\r\nI'm curious what was the system design for RefundableCrowdsale + RefundVault",
